<b>Mac an Fhucadair</b> ‘son of the fuller’. This surname is also very common among African Americans.","History: The name was brought to North America from northern England and Scotland independently by many different bearers in the 17th and 18th centuries. Samuel Walker came to Lynn, MA, <i>c.</i> 1630; Philip Walker was in Rehoboth, MA, in or before 1643. The surname was also established in VA before 1650; a Thomas Walker, born in 1715 in King and Queen County, VA, was a physician, soldier, and explorer."],"variants":[{"name":"Walcher","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Gunther, Hans, Horst, Klaus.","German: variant of   Walker   or   Walch  ."]},{"name":"Waker","meanings":["English (Yorkshire):","either a nickname for a watchful person or an occupational name for a watchman, from Middle English <i>waker</i> ‘watchful, vigilant’ (Old English <i>wacor</i>) and the derived noun.","mostly an early Modern English and Scots variant of   Walker  ."]},{"name":"Fuller","meanings":["English: occupational name for a dresser of cloth, from Middle English <i>fuller</i> ‘fuller of cloth’ (partly from Old English <i>fullere</i>, partly from Old French <i>fouleor</i>, <i>foleur</i>, Latin <i>fullo</i>). Raw cloth had to be fulled, i.e. scoured, cleansed, and thickened by beating or trampling it in water, a process also known as <i>walking</i> or <i>tucking</i>, hence the surnames   Walker   and   Tucker   alongside <i>Fuller</i>. These three terms and surnames are characteristic of different parts of England. In general, in Middle English, <i>Fuller</i> is southern and eastern, while <i>Walker</i> belongs to the west and north and <i>Tucker</i> is southwestern. Compare   Fullen  .","English: variant of   Fullard   with loss of <i>-d</i>.","German (<b>Füller</b>): occupational name for a person whose work involved filling, such as a dauber, or a nickname for a gourmand or glutton. Compare   Filler  ."]},{"name":"Walke","meanings":["German: metonymic occupational name for a fuller, from Middle High German <i>walke</i> ‘fulling mill’. Compare   Walker  .","English (Devon): variant of   Walk  ."]},{"name":"Walck","meanings":["German: variant of   Walker   or   Walch  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Ealifia Walker (m) was born in 1400, in Castle, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom. She married William Walker in 1430, in England. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. She died in 1512, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 112."},"et":{"1400–1512":"1400–1512","1409–1475":"1409–1475","1420–1461":"1420–1461","1437–1466":"1437–1466","1437":"1437","1512":"1512","1400":"1400","1466":"1466","1420":"1420","1475":"1475","1430":"1430","1461":"1461","1409":"1409","Pembroke Castle, England, United Kingdom":"Castle, Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Boarstall, Buckinghamshire, England":"Boarstall, Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Barton, Berkshire, England":"Berkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1400–1512":"1400–1512","1409–1475":"1409–1475","1420–1461":"1420–1461","1437–1466":"1437–1466","1437":"1437","1512":"1512","1400":"1400","1466":"1466","1420":"1420","1475":"1475","1430":"1430","1461":"1461","1409":"1409","Pembroke Castle, England, United Kingdom":"Castle, Northumberland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Boarstall, Buckinghamshire, England":"Boarstall, Buckinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Barton, Berkshire, England":"Berkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1400–1512":"1400–1512","1409–1475":"1409–1475","1420–1461":"1420–1461","1437–1466":"1437–1466","1437":"1437","1512":"1512","1400":"1400","1466":"1466","1420":"1420","1475":"1475","1430":"1430","1461":"1461","1409":"1409","Pembroke Castle, England, United Kingdom":"Castle, Northumberland, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Boarstall, Buckinghamshire, England":"Boarstall, Buckinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre,